claim.claim-text:
A reaction container according to either one of claim 1 and claim 2, wherein

said wide-mouthed piping part and said narrow-mouthed piping part are separately formed;

a hole portion is piercingly provided in the center of a bottom portion of said wide-mouthed piping part; said narrow-mouthed piping part has an aperture edge portion along an outer circumference of the aperture thereof and enclosing the aperture; said narrow-mouthed piping part is provided such that, excluding for said aperture edge portion, it is able to pass through said hole portion; said narrow-mouthed piping part downwardly protrudes from said hole portion of the wide-mouthed piping part such that it passes through said hole portion; said aperture edge portion is installed on the bottom of said wide-mouthed piping part; and said film is attached to said aperture edge portion of said narrow-mouthed piping part.

A reaction container system: a nozzle head provided with a suction-discharge mechanism that performs the suction and the discharge of gases, and one or two or more nozzles that detachably mount dispensing tips, whereby the suction and the discharge of liquids is possible by means of the suction-discharge mechanism;

a container group that has, at the very least, a reaction container according to any one of claim 1 to claim 11 whereby a solution for reaction, or a portion thereof, used for reactions is housed or is housable;

a nozzle transfer mechanism that makes an interval between said nozzle head and said container group relatively movable;

a temperature controller whereby temperature control of the interior of said reaction container is possible;

a light guide stage provided to said nozzle head that has two or more linking portions that are directly or indirectly linkable with said housing part for reactions of said reaction container, to which the ends of one or two or more light guide portions that optically connect with the interior of the linked housing part for reactions are provided;

a connecting end arranging body that has an arranging surface that supports two or more connecting ends that are provided corresponding to said respective linking portions and provided with a back end of said light guide portions, in which the ends thereof are provided to the linking portions, by arranging them along a predetermined path;

a measuring device provided approaching or making contact with said arranging surface that, by means of optical connections with the respective connecting ends, is able to receive light based on an optical state within said reaction container,

wherein said respective connecting ends provided along said predetermined path of said connecting end arranging body, and said respective measuring ends, mutually move such that they become successively optically connected.
